# ✅ To-do-list App

A full-stack task management app built with **Express.js**, **MongoDB**, and a frontend (e.g., React/Vite) compiled into a static `dist/` folder.

## 🛠 Features

- Add, edit, delete tasks
- Mark tasks as completed
- View total vs. completed task count
- REST API with MongoDB backend
- Serves built frontend using Express

---

## ⚙️ Technologies Used

- **Frontend**: React + Vite (assumed)
- **Backend**: Express.js
- **Database**: MongoDB with Mongoose
- **Others**: Morgan, CORS

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/To-do-list.git
cd To-do-list
npm install
# Ubuntu
sudo systemctl start mongod

# or using brew on Mac
brew services start mongodb-community
# If using Vite
npm run build
#Run server
npm run dev
```
